review_blob: My favorite beer in college.  We couldnt get enough.  Now I cant find it at all...  We loved the puzzle caps.  Light taste.  Light aroma.  Light everything.

Another great seasonal from Pyramid.  The palate is smooth and robust.  I drink it like water after I mow the lawn for the last time in October...  It is sometime on tap at the brewery across from Safeco field in Seattle.  Great to pound a few back on a Saturday afternoon and watch the mariners play.
This bad boy will definately tilt your kilt.  On tap this can be a damaging beer.  Puts you on your hind end easy.
One of my favorites.  Great buzz after two of them.  The flavor is great as well.  They serve it at the Red Dog here in town.
beer_name: Mac and Jacks African Amber Ale

review_blob: My favorite Lite beer.  Low carbs to boot.  Drink enough of them and you get a buzz.  What more do you want?

This beer (?) reminds me of a drink we made when I worked at Scout camp.  We called ia a "Flaming Moe" after the Simpsons bartender.  We would buy a 40 oz bottle of Lucky lager and drink it doen to the label and then pour in a berry winecoooler.  It was great for those hot summer afternoons at Camp Parsons on the ol Hood Canal...

Great beer.  One of my favorites.  Great flavor and taste.  Light head and a great color.  I can only find it at the Pyramid Brewery in Seattle across from Safeco Field.  I always slam six or so of them before a Mariners game.

Another great product from Pyramid.  I really like the ambers and the wheats and this is one for the books.  I would love to fing it on tap somewhere.  Just saw it tonight in Safeway.  I hope that it joins pyramid in its regular line-up,and not just a seasonal beer.
